First of all, I need to modify my answer from the following page; I DO NOT teach Bioinformatics and DO NOT plan in including it as it does not fit in well the core content of an introductory organismal biology course (diversity of life, ecology, and evoluion) course.  Furthermore, while I feel bioinformatics should be introduced in some meaningful way in the undergraduate education.  It might not be appropriate to teach it in the 1 year introductory biology major series because there is already a great may things to teach and we need to constantly remind our selves to focus on the fundamentals of the discipline.  It is this need to focus on the fundamentals in light of all the things that we may feel students "just have to learn"  (i.e., all the material hat we are tempted to try and squeeze into a course to its ultimate detriment) that prevents me from including bioinformatics.
